---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import VerdictArtifact from '../components/VerdictArtifact.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Can you stop it in time? · Intervene"
  description="Most organisations have governance, controls and accountability. Almost none have measured whether intervention is still possible when it matters. AGDA measures it, and signs the answer."
  current="home"
>
  <!-- 1 · DOORWAY. Loud. -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1 class="display-xl">Can you stop it <em>in time?</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Your most consequential system is running right now. If it turns, the
        clock starts.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-note">It is a fair question. Almost no one has measured the answer.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="/Intervene/contact/" class="btn">Find out where you stand</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2 · Recognition. Quiet. -->
  <section class="block quiet">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <h2 class="h2">The honest answer is usually <em>“I think so.”</em></h2>
      <p class="body">
        You have a framework. An accountable owner, documented controls, an
        escalation policy. All of it real, and all of it necessary. None of it
        measures the one thing that decides the outcome: at 3am, is the person
        who can halt the system reachable, authorised, and certain enough to act
        while acting still costs less than waiting?
      </p>
      <p class="body muted">Most leaders sense this. Almost none have measured it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3 · Recognition scenario. Quiet, building. -->
  <section class="block quiet">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="window-head">
        <h2 class="h2">You have probably watched <em>a version of this.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede muted">
          Not because anyone was careless. Because authority moves through
          people, and people move slower than the harm.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="window-grid reveal" role="list">
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+0</span><span class="stage-label">System event</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">No signal yet.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">The system starts producing decisions outside its limits. Nothing has reached anyone with the authority to act.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+6h</span><span class="stage-label">Operations</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">Noticed, not stoppable.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">Someone sees the deviation. They cannot halt the system, and the route to who can is unclear.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+18h</span><span class="stage-label">Management</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">Still compounding.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">It reaches management. Authority to halt is still being established. The cost grows by the hour.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage critical">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip warn">T+36h</span><span class="stage-label">Board</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">The window has closed.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">The board is informed. The moment for low-cost intervention has already passed.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="window-foot">The chain was never tested before it had to hold.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4 · THE GAP. Heavy. The turn. -->
  <section class="gap">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <span class="label gap-label">The measurement gap</span>
      <h2 class="h2 gap-h">You have measured almost <em>everything except this.</em></h2>
      <p class="gap-body">
        Capital. Model performance. Control coverage. Incident counts. Audit
        findings. The one factor that decides whether harm becomes irreversible,
        whether intervention is still possible when it matters, is the one
        nobody puts a number to.
      </p>
      <p class="gap-realisation">
        <span>You have governance.</span>
        <span>You have controls.</span>
        <span>You have accountability.</span>
        <strong>You have never measured whether intervention remains possible when it matters.</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="gap-refrain">Which means you cannot yet answer the question. <em>Can you stop it in time?</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5 · THE VERDICT. Climax. The only colour on the page. -->
  <section class="block verdict">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="verdict-lead">
        <span class="label">The verdict</span>
        <h2 class="h2">There is a deterministic, signed <em>way to find out.</em></h2>
        <p class="body muted">
          AGDA runs your system against that one question and returns a verdict,
          not a maturity score. The same inputs produce the same result every
          time. A regulator can confirm it independently.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="verdict-stage reveal">
        <VerdictArtifact />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6 · CLOSE. Sparse. The refrain returns. -->
  <section class="block close">
    <div class="wrap close-wrap">
      <h2 class="close-q">Can you stop it <em>in time?</em></h2>
      <p class="close-line">Now there is a way to know. One conversation to scope it. Confidential.</p>
      <a href="/Intervene/contact/" class="btn">Get your verdict</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Two black pillars: the question (doorway) and the gap (the turn).
     Colour appears once, in the verdict. Tempo: loud, quiet, quiet,
     heavy, climax, sparse. */
  .hero,
  .gap {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .hero ::selection,
  .gap ::selection { background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); }

  /* 1 · Hero */
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(96px, 14vh, 184px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(80px, 11vh, 152px);
  }
  .hero .display-xl { max-width: 14ch; color: var(--paper); }
  .hero-sub {
    margin: clamp(32px, 5vh, 56px) 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 1.6vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--paper);
    max-width: 34ch;
  }
  .hero-note {
    margin: 20px 0 0;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.66);
    max-width: 44ch;
  }
  .hero-cta { margin-top: 48px; }
  .hero .btn { background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--paper); }
  .hero .btn:hover { background: var(--paper-mid); border-color: var(--paper-mid); }

  /* Quiet recognition sections: narrower, lighter, restrained. */
  .block.quiet .h2 { max-width: 22ch; font-size: clamp(28px, 3.2vw, 44px); }
  .wrap-narrow .body { margin: 24px 0 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .window-head { margin-bottom: 64px; }
  .window-head .h2 { max-width: 20ch; }
  .window-head .lede { margin-top: 20px; max-width: 50ch; }
  .window-grid {
    list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); column-gap: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .window-grid > .stage {
    padding: 28px 0; display: grid; gap: 12px; align-content: start;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px);
    transition: opacity 480ms cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1), transform 480ms cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);
  }
  .window-grid.in > .stage { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 120ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 240ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 360ms; }
  .chip-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .time-chip {
    display: inline-block; background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; padding: 5px 9px; line-height: 1;
  }
  .time-chip.warn { background: var(--warn); }
  .stage-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .window-grid .h3 { font-size: 21px; margin: 4px 0 0; }
  .window-grid p { max-width: 32ch; margin: 0; }
  .window-foot {
    margin: 44px 0 0; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: clamp(18px, 1.8vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--ink); max-width: 40ch;
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .window-grid > .stage { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition: none; }
  }

  /* 4 · The gap. Heavy. */
  .gap { padding: clamp(104px, 14vh, 176px) 0; }
  .gap-label {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); padding-bottom: 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .gap-h { color: var(--paper); max-width: 18ch; font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 64px); }
  .gap-body {
    margin: 28px 0 0; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .gap-realisation {
    margin: 56px 0 0; padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
    display: grid; gap: 10px;
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.25; max-width: 26ch;
  }
  .gap-realisation > span { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); }
  .gap-realisation > strong { color: var(--paper); font-weight: 600; max-width: 30ch; margin-top: 6px; }
  .gap-refrain {
    margin: 40px 0 0; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 16px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.66); max-width: 48ch;
  }
  .gap-refrain em { color: var(--paper); font-style: italic; }

  /* 5 · The verdict. Climax. */
  .verdict { padding-top: clamp(96px, 12vh, 144px); padding-bottom: clamp(96px, 12vh, 144px); }
  .verdict-lead { max-width: 40ch; margin-bottom: 56px; }
  .verdict-lead .label { padding-bottom: 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .verdict-lead .h2 { max-width: 22ch; }
  .verdict-lead .body { margin-top: 20px; max-width: 52ch; }
  .verdict-stage { display: flex; justify-content: center; }

  /* 6 · Close. Sparse. */
  .close { padding-top: clamp(112px, 16vh, 200px); padding-bottom: clamp(112px, 16vh, 200px); }
  .close-wrap { display: grid; gap: 28px; justify-items: start; }
  .close-q {
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 96px); letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1.0; margin: 0; max-width: 14ch; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .close-line { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; max-width: 44ch; }

  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .window-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 24px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .window-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
